&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analyst, Continuous Improvement, Operational Excellence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary/Objective:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Operational Excellence (OpEX) team is constructing a foundational, scalable, and agile operations platform for Factor that supports market share growth and enables best-in-class customer experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an Analyst, Continuous Improvement, Operational Excellence to join the team. You will be working on cross-functional transformation projects for our Factor business. Within this role you will provide analyses and support projects aimed at solving complex problems impacting our operations and customer experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Associate Director, OpEX, you will play a key role in improving Customer Experience and errors reporting, data consolidation, and troubleshooting any issues as they arise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work closely with local and network planning, launch teams, automation and engineering, and maintenance, reliability, and engineering (M&amp;amp;RE) teams to improve the critical input metrics for the DC by prioritizing and channeling resources to address gaps in these inputs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Functions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Provide analytics on a variety of fulfillment and customer topics,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;including customer reported errors, forecasted volumes, and fulfillment planning inputs.&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Improve our analytics capability:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;identify inefficiencies and gaps within our analytics process and work to streamline and improve the way the team operates.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exemplify best practice:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;develop processes, analysis methodologies and dashboards to increase efficiency and consistency within the fulfillment functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enable data-drivenness for better decisions making:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;create innovative solutions that enable colleagues to easily track, report and identify trends and opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Identify growth opportunities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;analyze business performance to identify opportunities to invest operations resources more efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use your technical skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;quickly learn about our data infrastructure, extract and aggregate data with complex SQL queries, make clear summaries for stakeholders in visualization software, or apply advanced analytics methodologies using Python/R where appropriate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–3 years of experience in inventory control, warehouse operations, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with ERP or WMS systems; ability to perform accurate data entry and transaction auditing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail-oriented with strong organizational and documentation skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working on a production or warehouse floor in a fast-paced, perishable goods environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Excel or Google Sheets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Associate&#39;s or Bachelor&#39;s degree in Business, Supply Chain, or a related field preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
