&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a business-oriented leader to architect and own the financial operating model for our entire cloud infrastructure. This isn&#39;t a reporting role; you are the single-threaded owner responsible for optimizing one of the company&#39;s largest technology investments. Your mission is to transform our cloud spend from a complex cost center into a predictable, efficient engine for innovation. You will report to senior leadership and be empowered to support the negotiation of multi-million dollar contracts, drive cultural change across engineering, and provide the financial clarity required for strategic business decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cultural Change:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as the evangelist for Cloud FinOps. Champion a culture of cost ownership across our engineering organization by empowering teams with the dashboards, insights, and training needed to make cost an integral part of their design and operating principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Governance &amp;amp; Visibility: &lt;/strong&gt;Architect a system of governance and accountability. Design and implement a universal resource tagging strategy, moving beyond simple reporting to create robust showback/chargeback models that give engineering teams true ownership of their spend.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Optimization &amp;amp; Efficiency:&lt;/strong&gt; Drive a company-wide optimization program. Go beyond &quot;low-hanging fruit&quot; to create a continuous optimization program, partnering with engineering to refactor applications for cost, adopt new pricing models, and eliminate systemic waste.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commercial Strategy &amp;amp; Negotiation:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop and execute the strategy to lead negotiations with our cloud vendors, right-sizing our commitments to align with our business strategy and eliminating financial risk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Forecasting &amp;amp; Budgeting:&lt;/strong&gt; Build and operate our data-driven forecasting model. Partner directly with the Tech and Finance organizations to eliminate spending volatility and provide the business with a reliable cloud budget and accurate forecast.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are a seasoned leader who operates at the intersection of technology and finance. You are just as comfortable debating architectural trade-offs with a principal engineer as you are presenting a business case to a CFO. You are a strong team player who loves to share knowledge, enable others, and provide and receive feedback.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proven Experience: &lt;/strong&gt;A track record of 7+ years in dedicated Cloud FinOps or Cloud Financial Management roles, with clear success in managing significant AWS spend.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mastery of Cloud Economics:&lt;/strong&gt; Deep expertise in AWS cost structures, including the nuances of Savings Plans, Reserved Instances, Spot, and the Cost and Usage Report (CUR).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data-Driven Strategist&lt;/strong&gt;: Exceptional analytical and financial modeling skills. You don&#39;t just create dashboards; you build data-driven business cases to influence executive-level decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Credibility &amp;amp; Influence: &lt;/strong&gt;You have hands-on experience and a proven ability to partner with engineering teams to optimize application architecture for cost. You can engage and communicate complex ideas effectively to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proven Negotiator:&lt;/strong&gt; Demonstrable, material experience leading or participating in large-scale commercial negotiations with a major cloud vendor.&l

